The number 4️⃣ is considered an unlucky number in many East Asian cultures because of the very similar pronunciation of "four" and "death" ☠️ in their language.  If you step onto an elevator 🛗, you might not see a button indicating the 4th, 14th, 24th etc floors because many buildings skip the number altogether. 😬 When choosing the telephone 📞 numbers and the vehicle 🚗 identification numbers, many people would avoid number 4. ❌

I've just received my GREEN CARD! 😭❤️ And that's my Sunday morning face, filled with gratitude. 🙏✨ 
And I didn't have to tie the knot 💒 with anyone to make this happen 😅! My closest friends know how much hard work, energy and time I invested in enduring this journey. But I made it – in the proper way! 💪🏻

In the realm of social media, people see only a small percentage of what I've gone through to reach where I am now. Through the ups and downs, the path was truly worthwhile.🙏 I never thought I'd achieve it so swiftly, though. I was prepared to wait for years before I could hold this card and the brochure “Welcome to the United States” in my hand. 🥹

Look at my story to see my reaction 😅🫶🏼
